Here’s why it’s not possible 🫡👇🏽

One of the key factors that contribute to teeth yellowing in vapers is the presence of nicotine. Nicotine can stain teeth over time, similar to how it does with traditional tobacco products. Additionally, the heat and chemicals in the vaping aerosol can cause damage to the enamel, the outer protective layer of teeth. As the enamel wears down, the underlying dentin, which is naturally yellow in color, becomes more visible, leading to teeth appearing yellow.

Overwhelming is literally an understatement 😂

Here’s my list of 5 things I’ve learned in my first year as a dental hygienist. ⠀
⠀
•Be prepared for anything. If your first day is at an established office, be ready to whip out that anesthetic because you may have to start on an SRP. It happened to me! 🙋🏽‍♀️ I was so nervous and that’s ok- I definitely had to do a little self talk calming my nerves down, but it was a success! ⠀
⠀
•Ask. Ask. Ask. If you need help with taking an x-ray or finding an instrument - don’t be afraid to ask! Even if you’re the only hygienist in the office, ask the front staff or even the dentist. We’ve all be there before. 🤷🏽‍♀️⠀
⠀
•Do your notes. If you have time to do your notes after your patient leaves the chair - DO IT! If you don’t have enough time, that’s ok too. I remember during my first few weeks, I did all of my notes at the end of my shift. This was totally fine because I’d write down important details on their route slips to make sure I’d remember to include them in my notes. So do your best to keep notes about each of your patients when you can. ⠀
⠀
•Watch the clock. Try your best to stay on time. It helped me a lot to know how long each doctor needed for an exam so that I could balance that with the time needed to clean/sterilize my instruments and take care of my patients. Running behind sucks! It happens to all of us- just try to stay ahead of it as best as you can! ⏰⠀
⠀
•Be confident. I always say this- but you have to believe in yourself and your ability to provide the treatment that you have spent years learning. YOU GOT THIS 🙌🏼 ⠀

..⠀

A reflection on my recent journey around the sun- Despite the weight of the world on my heart due to the ongoing struggles of our brothers and sisters in Palestine, I found it challenging to celebrate. This weekend I hosted a wonderful workshop with Dentsply and hosted an intimate gathering with a few close friends, embracing a Palestinian-themed Friendsgiving. 

We came together to share our emotions and offer prayers for our fellow human beings enduring hardship. The warmth of everyone's presence was truly special, reaffirming my belief in the power of bringing people together. I remain hopeful that the world will continue to unite and advocate for those who lack a voice.

This past year marked a period of significant personal growth for me. I navigated through a challenging phase, finally glimpsing the light at the end of the tunnel. I bid farewell to certain aspects of my life, making space for new opportunities to blossom.

I want to conclude this with a heartfelt prayer (duaa) for the people of Palestine and all those currently enduring suffering around the world:

please ease the burdens and suffering of our brothers and sisters in Palestine and every corner of the world where hardship prevails. Ameen. 🤲🏼
